## ğŸ› ï¸ Installation

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/adammerrill/AstroJS-template.git
cd AstroJS-template
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
pnpm install
```

This will install all required dependencies and set up git hooks via Husky.

### 3. Environment Configuration

Create your local environment file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Configure the following **required** variables:

```bash
# Base URL for sitemap generation and canonical URLs
SITE_URL="http://localhost:4321"

# Storyblok Access Token (Settings â†’ Access Tokens â†’ Preview)
STORYBLOK_TOKEN="your_storyblok_preview_token_here"

# Optional: Analytics and monitoring
# GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID="G-XXXXXXXXXX"
# SENTRY_DSN="https://xxxxx@sentry.io/xxxxx"
```

> **âš ï¸ Security Note**: Never commit `.env` files to version control. The `.gitignore` file is pre-configured to exclude them.

#### Getting Your Storyblok Token

1. Log in to your [Storyblok account](https://app.storyblok.com/)
2. Navigate to **Settings â†’ Access Tokens**
3. Copy your **Preview** token (not the Public token)
4. Paste it into your `.env` file

<!-- TODO: Add screenshots of Storyblok token location -->

### 4. Sync Content Types

Synchronize Astro with Storyblok schema:

```bash
pnpm astro sync
```

This generates TypeScript types for your Storyblok content types.

### 5. Start Development Server

```bash
pnpm dev
```

The application will be available at [http://localhost:4321](http://localhost:4321).

### Optional: Mobile Network Testing

Test on mobile devices connected to the same network:

```bash
pnpm dev:host
```

Access via your computer's local IP address (e.g., `http://192.168.1.x:4321`).

